      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model (bilinear isotropic hardening for Ti-6Al-4V, linear elastic for UHMWPE surrogates) justified by literature and coupon data. Contact formulation appropriate for screw-rod interface.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening model for Ti-6Al-4V is consistent with published tensile data and coupon test results. Linear elastic UHMWPE surrogate is appropriate given the small-strain regime below 40 mm displacement. Augmented Lagrange contact at screw-rod and rod-block interfaces captures frictional sliding. Model form adequacy confirmed by comparison to three independent FEA implementations (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes). Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
