      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions (load rate, temperature, potting method) replicated across at least two independent condition variants or laboratories. Environmental controls documented.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single load rate (5 mm/min) and ambient temperature (23±2°C) per ASTM F1717. Two independent laboratories participated, providing inter-laboratory variability data, but only a single set of test conditions was explored. Variation in load rate or temperature was not assessed. This factor is below the required level 3; risk is accepted given the standardized ASTM F1717 protocol and the medium model risk level. Achieved level 2 does not meet required level 3 — noted as accepted gap per COU description."
    },
    {
